title Logical design

/'jBPM "Notes" (for claude)
- generate System.out.println in the same way as in the pniDesign (it is very useful when debugging).
- one step in UML can consist of more processes/tasks in jBPM (like: find building/PLACE).
- Keep the diagram order as it is, but in jBPM firstly do all FIND types and then all
  CREATE_OR_UPDATE types (try to find everything we need before we start creating/updating data).
  EXCEPTION: "find CPE:CAGE" (findCustomerSideCage) is a FIND that needs cpeCrossId, which is
  produced by "place CPE" (a CREATE). So it cannot run before the creates - it runs right after
  "place CPE". Every other FIND is moved to the front.
- This process is started by Automaton, not by ODIN directly. Automaton stores the request body
  in automaton.tmf_store and starts the process with a single start parameter "_order" (= tmf_store id).
  The first task ("get data from TMF_STORE") loads that body and extracts the input fields via JSONATA.
- Synchronous process: the final "Completed"/"Failed" link assembles a "response" Map that Automaton
  returns to ODIN as the HTTP body.
'/

