    /'SdcApiCall: "REST_API_CALL \n cross/updateEthLinkProviders"
    Description: Set networkSidePatchCord, opticalPath and customerSidePatchCord as providers of ethLinkCrossId (HTTP PUT).
    Type: CREATE_OR_UPDATE

    On Entry Action:
    ethLinkProviders = new java.util.ArrayList<Map<String, Object>>();

    Map<String, Object> networkSidePatchCord = new java.util.HashMap<>();
    networkSidePatchCord.put( "providerCrossId", networkSidePatchCordCrossId );
    networkSidePatchCord.put( "consumptionType", "MAIN" );
    networkSidePatchCord.put( "reversed", false );
    networkSidePatchCord.put( "orderNumber", 1 );
    networkSidePatchCord.put( "fibrilNumber", 1 );
    ethLinkProviders.add( networkSidePatchCord );

    Map<String, Object> opticalPath = new java.util.HashMap<>();
    opticalPath.put( "providerCrossId", opticalPathCrossId );
    opticalPath.put( "consumptionType", "MAIN" );
    opticalPath.put( "reversed", false );
    opticalPath.put( "orderNumber", 1 );
    opticalPath.put( "fibrilNumber", 1 );
    ethLinkProviders.add( opticalPath );

    Map<String, Object> customerSidePatchCord = new java.util.HashMap<>();
    customerSidePatchCord.put( "providerCrossId", customerSidePatchCordCrossId );
    customerSidePatchCord.put( "consumptionType", "MAIN" );
    customerSidePatchCord.put( "reversed", false );
    customerSidePatchCord.put( "orderNumber", 1 );
    customerSidePatchCord.put( "fibrilNumber", 1 );
    ethLinkProviders.add( customerSidePatchCord );

    Data Inputs and Assignments:
    apiUrl, String, _apiCallUrl
    routeMap.domain, String, "REST_API_CALL"
    routeMap.source, String, "cross/v1/link"
    dataMap.projectName, String, crossProjectName
    dataMap.crossId, String, ethLinkCrossId
    dataMap.providers, java.util.List, ethLinkProviders

    Data Outputs and Assignments:
    httpStatusCode, Integer, httpStatusCode
    message, String, message

    Gateway:
    If httpStatusCode != 200 => set "message" as "errorMessage" and invoke Intermediate Link "Failed".
    Default => invoke Intermediate Link "Completed".
    '/

